        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 7 at 5:21PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 521 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wadley, or 12 miles south of Louisville, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Alexander, Sardis, Girard, Midville, Burke County Airport, Colemans
Lake, Magruder, and Rosier.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 600 PM EDT for east central
Georgia...and central South Carolina.</instruction>
